Job Description

Responsibilities:

• Manage Information Technology team in Hong Kong, including all offices and warehouses, and provide IT support to corporate users;
• Enhance system serviceability, online stability, provide solutions and troubleshoot hardware and software issues;
• Ensure the development and operation of IT infrastructure are in compliance with the technical, system security and project management standards;
• Liaise with IT service providers / vendors and other third-parties;
• Oversee and determine time frames for major IT projects including system updates, upgrades, migrations and outages;
• Communicate and arrange awareness training for business users;
• Manage, train, and mentor IT staff;
• Prepare IT proposal, budget, technical documentation and system specification;
• Formulating IT policies and procedures;
• Hands on experience in Oracle / MSSQL / AD / Windows server / VMWare / VSAN, Firewall administration, Systems Tools, Local Systems Infra / application Team and WMS system;
• Responsible for System HA / DR infrastructure design, implementation and maintenance;
• Perform system administration, monitoring and capacity management; and
• Understand and satisfy Cyber Security requirements.

 Requirements:                 

• Degree holder in Computer Science or Information System;
• Current holder of MCSE, CCNA, and ITIL 4 Foundation;
• A minimum of 10 years’ experience in multiple areas of technology, including systems infrastructure and application;
• With strong and broad understanding in multiple technical domains including but not limited to: Business Applications, Microsoft O365, Microsoft Exchange, Sharepoint, Azure, Network and Firewalls etc;
• A good team player with analytical & problem-solving skills, self-motivation, positive attitude, fast-learning, energetic, able to perform in challenging environment;
• Good knowledge in developing Windows network, Linux and PC infrastructure;
• Strong leadership and management skills, proven ability to manage IT team to achieve timelines and objectives;
• Proficiency in both written and spoken English, Chinese and Mandarin; and
• Can work under pressure and fast-paced working environment.

DEAR TALENT, YOUR MOVE!

Being the new rising airline since 2013, we are the Hong Kong’s only Low Cost Carrier (LCC) offering you safe and flexible service options to Hong Kong and beyond.

We’re on a mission to inspire you to be different, to shake things up, to inspire the spirit of adventure by bringing you to fascinating destinations that few others serve.

Spread your wings and fly with us!

What will you do? 

Lead a small team to maintain daily IT Infrastructure operation to support internal users within SLA under ITIL standard;
Support Security team to handle security events in IT infrastructure environment;
Support internal audit to assess different IT areas;
Develop and maintain formal guidelines, policies, and procedures to ensure the smooth operation;
Manage external vendor to provide technical support on corporate IT Infrastructure with emphasis on the internal network, servers, Microsoft office365 environment and cloud infrastructure;
Manage external vendor to provide technical support on Airport IT Infrastructure with emphasis on Express IP, AviNet, ACARS and EDI about Cargo / Crew / Passenger Information Filing;
Plan, setup, lead and manage the IT Infrastructure and End-user Technology Strategy including disaster recovery planning;
Research on new technology, identify technology gaps, develop and deploy Infrastructure solutions;
Remediate Risk & Vulnerability for Infrastructure and End-user computing;
Drive the continuous improvement to all IT Infrastructure related services;
Determine how to leverage enabling technologies to implement innovative IT infrastructure solutions to support the business
Coach and mentor team members;
Travel occasionally for new station setup/support; 
Support ad-hoc duties as assigned.

We are a perfect match, if you are:

University graduate in Computer Technology or related discipline;
Minimum 6 years of related working experiences in IT security with 2 years of supervisor post;
Strong technical knowledge in all aspects of IT Infrastructure especially in Microsoft Office365, Fortinet, Azure/Alibaba cloud and End-user computing;
Sound Knowledgeable on SOC, DLP and SIEM;
Certification on networking (such as CCNA, CCNP, CCIE);
ITILv3 Foundation Certification is a must;
Basic knowledge of common information security management frameworks, such as ISO 27001, CobiT, ITIL, PCI DSS.

Your Future Work Life?

Work flexibly with staggered working hours and flexible workplace
Dress Casual and Smart everyday
Work in a newly-designed office with open seating, stylish breakout areas, game room, gym and free coffee…
Work with a group of energetic and multicultural professionals (up to 50 nationalities!)
Have great fun in Snack Friday, New Year Market, Fly with your Kids Day, Basketball Team…
Have your voice heard through Townhalls, Crew forums, CEO live sessions etc.

What will you enjoy?

Fly anywhere we fly for free plus taxes during leisure with your friends and family
Special privileges to buy duty free products
Career Express


You will be inspired by our core values.
You will be inspired by our vibrant, efficient and entrepreneurial spirit. Join our fun, collaborative and reliable team to ignite your dream!


Interested? It’s time to have YOUR MOVE!
If you're ready to embark your adventure, start by clicking the ‘Apply now’ and get on the plane to fly with HK Express!

Responsibilities

Work with different internal teams to enhance business operations and process reengineering projects;
Define Business Process Reengineering scope and to-be process;
Documentation of process and workflows;
Assist in ad hoc tasks and other duties as required;
Prepare training materials & documents and provide training to user department

Requirements

Degree or above in IT, CS and Computing Engineering or equivalent;
3 years or above relevant experience in business analysis/project management role;
Well-developed analytical and problem solving skills;
Excellent interpersonal and communication skill;
Excellent verbal and written skill in English and Chinese;
Deep intellectual curiosity, detail-oriented and independently;
Experience in SQL and programming skill will be an advantage;
Experience in managing and delivering process improvement / re-engineering / project management;
Understanding the operations in the Construction industry will be an advantage

Interested parties please apply with a detailed resume stating expected salary and date of availability to the HR Manager through fax at 2833 5441 or e-mail by clicking "APPLY NOW".

Company Website: https://xensetech.hk/

All personal data provided will be used strictly in accordance with our “Personal Information Collection Statement Pertaining to Recruitment”, a copy of which is available upon written request to us by E-mail.

