Our client, an financial institutions, with full SFC licenses, they are hiring an IT Manager for their IT team, the requirements is as follow:-   
Degree holder + 5+years related IT network, technical supports from financial institutions;  
Report to IT Director, work together with teammates to perform supporting for business users via email, telephone or in person; 
Experience of technical, infrastructure, network daily supports as well as to perform Level I scripting;
Develop operational, installation, configuration and upgrade documentation for relevant technology components;
Perform regular tasks for computer operations, such as hardware, software installation, configuration on desktops, laptops, printers and mobile devices;
Follow standard guidelines and procedures for incident management, problem management etc;
Identify, isolate, resolve, escalate and close incident/problem ticket according to incident/problem management process;
Test all changes to networks, hardware, software, and hosted applications;
Experience in provision computing resources, capacity planning for IT infrastructure and assist in IT procurement;
Maintain IT inventory and ensure the services are renewed within timeframe;
Provide the necessary report(s) with accuracy during regular reporting;
Assist in special project when is needed; 
Good English and Fluent Cantonese;
Independent and good communication skill;
5 working days with full employee benefits. 
Interested candidates, please send full resume (in MS WORD format), with current and expected salary to us or please click APPLY NOW to submit your application. 

Ref: IT- 30353

Information provided by candidates with be treated in strict confidence and will only be used for recruitment related purposes. All information on unsuccessful candidates with be deleted from our files within 6 months.

Responsibilities

       Engage in advanced technology projects of AI, IoT, VR/AR/MR and Robotics;
       Conduct functional design and development;
       Research and participate in new technology development;
       Responsible for development, enhancement and maintenance for applications
       Provide support to application systems including trouble shooting, bug fixing and ad-hoc queries
       Conduct research and evaluate emerging software technologies

Requirements

       Degree or above in IT, CS and Computing Engineering or equivalent;
       1 year or above relevant experience in business analyst, advanced technology analyst or equivalent; 
       Passion in new advanced technology;
       Well-developed analytical and problem solving skills;
       Excellent interpersonal and communication skill;
       Excellent verbal and written skill in English and Chinese;
       Deep intellectual curiosity, detail-oriented and independently;
       Knowledge in one or more of the following areas will be an advantage:
Flutter / React Native / Swift / Kotlin
Latest technology (e.g. IoT, AI, Robotics, Blockchain)
API integrations
Edge and Cloud computing
UI / UX design concepts
 Knowledge of Construction will be an advantage

Interested parties please apply with a detailed resume stating expected salary and date of availability to the HR Manager through fax at 2833 5441 or e-mail by clicking "APPLY NOW".

